title: Lake Travis Senior Services—Downsizing Together
description:
Seniors Real Estate Specialist® Cyndi Cummings will share tips and tricks for downsizing and how joining a Downsizer Club can help us all share experiences and great ideas! Turnkey Transitions® and The Cummings Home Team offer compassionate, expert guidance for downsizing, rightsizing, and simplifying your life, helping your family make the right decisions that may arise with your home.

We are thrilled to partner with Lake Travis Senior Services for their ongoing speaker series. Each month, LTSS will dive into a timely, informational topic that impacts aging adults and their loved ones. Sessions will be led by one or more experts in a variety of fields.

title: Yoga for Brain & Nerve Health
description:
Join certified yoga instructor Adrian Langford for a gentle chair yoga class designed to strengthen and improve brain-body connections. Ideal for those with cognitive impairment, brain fog, ADHD, Parkinson’s, or anxiety. Props (blocks & straps) recommended.

Adrian specializes in Yoga for Brain & Nerve Health, Yoga Nidra, and Mindfulness-Based Stress Reduction (MBSR). With 12+ years of experience, she teaches adults of all levels, including those with limited mobility. She is currently working on 300 YTT and is a Certified Yoga Instructor for Nerve Disorders.

title: Chair Yoga
description:
Join registered yoga teacher Monika Orr for a session of chair yoga—a gentle practice in which postures are performed while seated. Chair yoga increases flexibility, strength and body awareness. The benefits also include muscle toning, reduced stress levels, better breathing habits, better sleep and an overall sense of well-being. Anyone who finds traditional mat yoga too challenging (for any of a myriad of reasons) can benefit. In chair yoga, you do not get up and down from the floor, there is no weight bearing on the wrists and shoulders, and much less risk of falling or injury.

All ages and abilities welcome. Please wear comfortable clothing and bring a water bottle.

title: CANCELED - Sound Bath
description:
A Sound Bath is a meditative experience in which musical instruments like singing bowls are used to relax, realign and re-energize the body and mind. Participants gather around these musical instruments while instructor Cassandra guides you into a deep, calming state. The term “bath” is used because participants are bathing in the sound as well as the vibrations the sound waves put off. These vibrations are incredibly calming as well, with the goal being to help stimulate your body into restoration as well as clearing out any negative emotions or energies that serve you no purpose.

Please bring a mat and any other items you might need to feel comfortable such as a pillow, blanket, or eye mask.

description: In partnership with Divine Canines and Canine Companions, Bow Wow Reading gives children the opportunity to practice reading to a certified therapy dog! Readers are given a 15-minute private session to practice in a calm and non-judgemental environment.
